title: Chris Matthews doesn’t know trees exist

author: Matt Walsh
description:
Today on the Matt Walsh Show, the Trump Administration has been doing quite a lot over its first three months in office. Now, we need Congress to pass laws codifying all of the things that Trump has done—so, why isn’t that happening? Where is Congress? Also, the House did succeed in passing an election integrity bill called the SAVE Act. The Democrats say that this bill will make it almost impossible for married women to vote. How could that possibly be the case? And Tim Pool upsets many conservatives with his take on the Austin Metcalf murder. We’ll listen to his case and evaluate. And the governor of Colorado just signed a bill effectively abolishing the Second Amendment in the state.
